	<express_ref linkend="parametric_representation:arm:Parametric_representation_arm.Parametric_representation_context" />
	for the <b>Definitional_representation</b>.
</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Parametric_representation_arm  Entity: Parametric_representation_context  
   <express_ref linkend="parametric_representation:arm:Parametric_representation_arm.Parametric_representation_context"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Parametric_representation_arm.Parametric_representation_context">
A <b>Parametric_representation_context</b> is a type of
	<express_ref linkend="foundation_representation:arm:Foundation_representation_arm.Representation_context"/>.
	A parametric representation context specifies that the representation of items of the referring representation exist
	in a parametric space rather than a two- or three- dimensional space.

	
</ext_description>
